  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed using a Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition variability and blood viscosity uncertainty across the five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study based on one-at-a-time perturbations was conducted informally during model development and its findings are summarized in the UQ report narrative. No structured sensitivity analysis record has been linked to this package.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
