    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, which is consistent with MRL 2 requirements for a Class II device with medium model influence. Uncertainty quantification was performed via Monte Carlo propagation and results confirm that NIH prediction intervals are within the decision-relevant uncertainty budget. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB device submission.",
